{{wikipedia}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From Hebrew [[שרה|שָׂרָה]] ''(Sara)'', "lady", "princess", which was originally converted from the given name [[שרי|שָׂרָי]], Sarai.

===Proper noun===
'''Sarah''' {{f}}

#(''Bible'') Wife of [[Patriarch]] [[Abraham]]. Mother of [[Isaac]].
#a female [[given name]]

